<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,662,905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,382,662,688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Nomenclatural notes</emphasis>
:— 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3382698314" collectionCode="BR" collectorName="Galeotti &amp; We" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
<bibRefCitation author="Martens, M. &amp; Galeotti, H." box="[415,730,662,689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="129 - 149" refId="ref6656" refString="Martens, M. &amp; Galeotti, H. (1845) Enumeratio synoptica plantarum phanerogamicarum ab Henrico Galeotti in regionibus Mexicanum collectarum. Bulletin de L'Academie Royale de Sciences et Belles-Letres de Bruxelles 12 (1): 129 - 149." type="journal article" year="1845">Martens and Galeotti (1845)</bibRefCitation>
cited one gathering in the protologue: 
<emphasis box="[1152,1300,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<collectorName box="[1152,1241,662,688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Galeotti</collectorName>
1242
</emphasis>
, and although no herbarium or exact specimen was specified, the original material collected by 
<collectorName box="[1011,1099,698,724]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Galeotti</collectorName>
was first deposited at herbarium 
<collectionCode box="[136,176,735,761]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">BR</collectionCode>
. 
<collectorName box="[190,226,735,761]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">We</collectorName>
traced 
<specimenCount box="[315,481,734,761]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
at 
<collectionCode box="[523,564,735,761]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">BR</collectionCode>
: 
<collectionCode box="[579,616,735,761]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">BR</collectionCode>
barcodes 000000552845 and 000000552904. One of the 
<emphasis box="[1296,1451,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Galeotti 1242</emphasis>
specimens at 
<collectionCode box="[287,324,771,797]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">BR</collectionCode>
(
<collectionCode box="[339,378,770,796]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">BR</collectionCode>
barcode 000000552845) is selected here as the 
<typeStatus box="[914,1017,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">lectotype</typeStatus>
for the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martens &amp; Galeotti" authorityYear="1845" box="[1173,1433,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="geminiflorum">
<emphasis box="[1173,1433,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Solanum geminiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</materialsCitation>
<emphasis box="[1432,1436,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,662,905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,393,806,832]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="M. Martens &amp; Galeotti" box="[429,690,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="geminiflora">
<emphasis box="[429,690,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Lycianthes geminiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an herb to shrub with white stellate corollas that occurs in the cloud forests of 
<collectingCountry box="[325,414,842,868]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sendtner 1846: 193) Bitter (1919: 494)" authorityName="Bitter" authorityPageNumber="494" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Sendtner" baseAuthorityPageNumber="193" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[687,1406,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heteroclita">
<emphasis box="[687,937,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Lycianthes heteroclita</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sendtner, O." box="[954,1181,842,868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="193 - 195" refId="ref7061" refString="Sendtner, O. (1846) Beschreibung einer neuen Gattung der Familie der Solanaceen, so wie von zwei neuen etwas abweichenden Arten der Gattung Solanum. Flora 29 (13): 193 - 195." type="journal article" year="1846">Sendtner 1846: 193</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Bitter, G." box="[1199,1406,842,868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="292 - 520" refId="ref6023" refString="Bitter, G. (1919) Die Gattung Lycianthes. Abhandlungen Herausgegeban vom Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 24: 292 - 520." type="journal article" year="1919">Bitter (1919: 494)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but occurs at higher elevations and has a smaller calyx. The relationship between the two species needs study.
</paragraph>
